# Environment Variables for kaadz.me

## Analytics
# Plausible Analytics (already configured in index.html)
# Domain: kaadz.me
# Script: https://plausible.io/js/script.js
# No API key required for client-side tracking

## Email Capture / Newsletter
# Option 1: Netlify Forms (already configured, no keys needed)
# Form name: llm-checklist
# Submissions viewable in Netlify dashboard

# Option 2: MailerLite (if you want to switch)
# VITE_MAILERLITE_API_KEY=your_mailerlite_api_key
# VITE_MAILERLITE_GROUP_ID=your_group_id

# Option 3: ConvertKit (if you want to switch)
# VITE_CONVERTKIT_API_KEY=your_convertkit_api_key
# VITE_CONVERTKIT_FORM_ID=your_form_id

## GitHub API (for star counts)
# Optional: Increase rate limit from 60 to 5000 requests/hour
# VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_personal_access_token
# Create token at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Required scopes: public_repo (read-only)

## Notes
# - Plausible is already set up and requires no configuration
# - Netlify Forms work automatically when deployed to Netlify
# - GitHub API works without token (60 requests/hour limit)
# - All VITE_ prefixed vars are exposed to client-side code
